{DIALOGUE}: Let's get some coffee and talk.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FBI ACADEMY GROUNDS - QUANTICO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE on Clarice and Crawford, as they walk along a sidewalk, sipping from paper cups.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The surveillance van trails them slowly, radios CRACKLING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Are you in trouble over this, Mr. Crawford?
{DIALOGUE}: Can Senator Martin do something to you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: I'm 53, Starling.
{DIALOGUE}: If I found Jimmy Hoffa on national TV, I'd still have to retire in two years.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not a consideration.
{DIALOGUE}: But you are...
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You've done enough.
{DIALOGUE}: If I keep you out of school any longer, you'll be recycled.
{DIALOGUE}: Cost you six months, at least.
{DIALOGUE}: I can guarantee you readmission here, but that's about it.
{META_DATA}: (he stops, looks at her)
{DIALOGUE}: Now's your chance, Starling.
{DIALOGUE}: Go back to class.
{DIALOGUE}: Leave Bill to me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: If you didn't want me chasing him, you shouldn't have taken me to that funeral home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at her steadily, then nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Lecter is still the key, I know he is.
{DIALOGUE}: Whatever he told me about Bill is just as good now as it was before.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Or just as worthless.
{DIALOGUE}: But I want you in Memphis, close to him.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe when he gets tired of toying with Senator Martin, he'll talk to you again.
{DIALOGUE}: There's a plane waiting for you now at the airstrip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles at this acknowledgment; he never thought she's quit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I lied to Lecter.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll need some kind of peace offering... Can I get the drawings from his cell?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Good idea.
{DIALOGUE}: Meantime, try to get a feel for Catherine Martin.
{DIALOGUE}: Her apartment, her friends... how he might've stalked her.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to the other two clinics, Minnesota and Ohio.
{META_DATA}: (he crumples his cup, tosses it)
{DIALOGUE}: Now's the hardest part, Starling.
{DIALOGUE}: Use your anger, don't let it keep you from thinking.
{DIALOGUE}: Just keep your eyes on Catherine.
{DIALOGUE}: We've got less than 30 hours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (hesitates)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Crawford... can those cops down there handle Dr. Lecter?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{META_DATA}: (grimly)
{DIALOGUE}: They'll use their best men.
{DIALOGUE}: But they better be paying attention...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. AIR NATIONAL GUARD HANGER - MEMPHIS, TENNESSEE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON Dr. Lecter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind his mask, the alert, searching eyes.
