{DIALOGUE}: Shit, he's just an ol' broke-dick.
{DIALOGUE}: Won't be no trouble as all if he don't flip out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOYLE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Chilton...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEW ANGLE - WIDER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as we see that we're in a vast, dusty hangar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Parked to one side: an EMS ambulance and four highway patrol cruisers; a dozen troopers stand quietly chatting and smoking over there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Prentiss is pacing impatiently, casting anxious glances towards the open hanger doorway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOYLE
{DIALOGUE}: If you'll please sign right here, sir, we'll have us a legal transfer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chilton instinctively pats his shirt pocket for his gold pen; it's gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He searches other pockets, with growing unhappiness.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOYLE
{DIALOGUE}: Use mine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PEMBRY
{DIALOGUE}: Here they come.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO BLACK STRETCH LIMOUSINES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: glide smoothly into the hangar, stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Secret Service agents pour out of the lead car, form a cordon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A driver opens the rear door of the second car, and Krendler steps out, followed by the Senator's assistant, with a briefcase, followed, as last, by the Senator herself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barely glancing around, she strides towards Lecter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEW ANGLE - DR. LECTER AND SEN. MARTIN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she stops, struck by the bizarre spectacle of his restraints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others instinctively keep a distance, but Chilton, with theatrical relish, unstraps and removes Dr. Lecter's mask.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHILTON
{DIALOGUE}: Senator Martin, meet Dr. Hannibal Lecter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stare at one another for a long moment: the Senator tense, almost haggard, the madman with his unearthly poise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Lecter, I've brought an affidavit guaranteeing your new rights... You'll want to read it before I sign.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He assistant unsnaps his briefcase, reaches for the form.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: I won't waste your time and Catherine's time bargaining for petty privileges.
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice Starling and that awful Jack Crawford have wasted far too much already.
{DIALOGUE}: I only pray they haven't doomed the poor girl... Let me help you now, and I'll trust you when it's all over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{DIALOGUE}: You have my word.
{DIALOGUE}: Paul?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Krendler raises a pad, poised to take notes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Buffalo Bill's real name is William Rubin.
{DIALOGUE}: I met him just once.
{DIALOGUE}: He was referred to me in April or May, 1980, by my patient Benjamin Raspail.
{DIALOGUE}: They were lovers, but Raspail had become very frightened.
{DIALOGUE}: Apparently Rubin had murdered a transient, and - done things with the skin.
{DIALOGUE}: He thought if I could cure Billy, then Billy'd be safe from the police, and he's be safe from Billy... Obviously, he was wrong.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: We need his address, a physical descr-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Did you nurse Catherine?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{META_DATA}: (pause; startled)
{DIALOGUE}: What...?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Did you breast-feed her?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He flicks his tongue obscenely.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: You son-of-a -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Senator stills him with a hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is trembling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{DIALOGUE}: Yes... I did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Toughened your nipples, didn't it...?
{META_DATA}: (a beat; then rapidly, bored)
{DIALOGUE}: Six foot one, strongly built, about 190 pounds.
{DIALOGUE}: Hair brown, eyes pale blue.
{DIALOGUE}: He'd be about 35 now.
{DIALOGUE}: He said he lived in Philadelphia, but may have lied.
{DIALOGUE}: That's really all I can remember, Senator - but if I think of any more, I'll let you know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{META_DATA}: (to the others)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go with it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start towards the car, but he calls out, stopping her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Senator Martin...!
{DIALOGUE}: You can't trust Jack Crawford or Clarice Starling.
{DIALOGUE}: It's such a game with these people.
{DIALOGUE}: They're determined to get the arrest for themselves.
{DIALOGUE}: The "collar," I think they say.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, Doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll keep it in mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, and Senator...?
{DIALOGUE}: Love you suit.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S BASEMENT - DAY (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON scraps of food - peas, chicken bones - lying on the cement floor of the pit, near the foil tray of a TV dinner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE (O.S.)
{META_DATA}: (muttering, feisty)
{DIALOGUE}: Close enough to fuck is close enough to fight...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is hunched over in concentration.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The plastic toilet bucket is on her lap, and she has yanked down its cotton string.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Get my legs round your neck, you goddamn creep, I'll send you home to Jesus...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER FINGERS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: are tying a chicken bone to the bucket's handle, where it meets the string.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other end of the string is tied to her wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SHE STANDS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: gathers the coiled string in one hand, and swings the bucket by its handle, calculating this distance up to the basement floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, Precious.
{DIALOGUE}: Time for a treat...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hurls the bucket upwards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE LIP OF THE OUBLIETTE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the bucket sails out, bounces LOUDLY, then falls back inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON THE DOG, PRECIOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: who is elsewhere in the basement, worrying a toy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She cocks an ear, making a low GROWL, then sets off to investigate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOWN IN THE PIT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catherine swings the bucket again, trying another cast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE BUCKET LANDS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: two feet beyond the pit's edge, rolls a bit, stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PRECIOUS TROTS UP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: then pauses, staring curiously towards...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VERY LOW ANGLE (DOG'S POV)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the enticing chicken bone, six feet away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It twitches as Catherine tugs on the string, edging the bucket back towards the pit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Precious with her tail wagging, BARKS - greedy but suspicious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: staring upwards, pulls again, even so gently, at the string.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: Preeeeecious...!
{DIALOGUE}: C'mon, boy, nice yummy bone... c'mon, you little shit...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PRECIOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: edges reluctantly closer... then suddenly rushes in, seizing the bone in her teeth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She tries to run away with it, but Catherine is pulling her towards the hole, working her like a hooked fish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her toenails scrabble as she tries to stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: stares desperately, unable to see how she's doing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Hang on, boy... hang on...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PRECIOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: still fights for the bone, GROWLING, as the bucket rocks precariously on the edge of the pit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long, seesaw battle... until finally, when one of her forelegs slips momentarily into the hole, she panics and lets go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bucket flops over the edge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: crouches, covering her head as the bucket bounces off her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Nooooo...!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE LITTLE DOG
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: furious, BARKS down at her, then trots away in disgust.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she sinks to the cold cement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slaps aside the foil tray, the scraps of food, sobbing in utter despair...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CATHERINE MARTIN'S APARTMENT - LIVING ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a framed photo of Sen. Martin and Catherine, held in Clarice's cotton-gloved hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Powdered fingerprints on the glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice glances up from the photo, smiles disarmingly at -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A young STATE TROOPER sitting in Catherine's easy chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles back at her, then relaxes, returns to his newspaper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He also wears gloves.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice closes the refrigerator door, glances around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A big REEL-TO-REEL TAPE RECORDER has been set up on the breakfast counter, attached to Catherine's phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two new red phones are hooked up as well.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BATHROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice slides open the medicine cabinet's mirror, looks inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches in, pokes carefully amongst the lotions.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ATTIC CRAWL-SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A ceiling hatch bangs open, sending up dust clouds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice, lit from underneath, pokes her head through, looking around.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flat on her back, Clarice wriggles out from under Catherine's bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sits up, brushing dust from her face and hair.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON an open, multi-tiered jewelry box, resting atop a bureau, as Clarice's fingers pick through costume jewelry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice closes the box, and is just turning away when a figure suddenly looms INTO SHOT, giving her a bad start; she cries out softly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Senator Martin is revealed, staring at her suspiciously.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you, please?
{DIALOGUE}: I thought the police were through in here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Clarice Starling, Senator.
{DIALOGUE}: FBI.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{META_DATA}: (softly, very angry)
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice Starling...
{META_DATA}: (calls out)
{DIALOGUE}: Paul?
{DIALOGUE}: Would you come in here, please...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Krendler enters from the hallway, looks at Clarice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEN. MARTIN
{DIALOGUE}: Miss Starling, you may know the Deputy Attorney General, Mr. Krendler.
{DIALOGUE}: Paul, this is the trainee that Jack Crawford sent to Lecter... She lied to him, pretending to have my authority, and thus jeopardized this entire investigation.
{DIALOGUE}: Now she has the further gall to invade my daughter's privacy, again without permission.
{DIALOGUE}: If her little games have killed my baby...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Overcome, she hurries from the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Krendler shuts the door behind her, points sternly at Clarice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: You're out of line, Starling, and you're off this case.
{DIALOGUE}: Back to Quantico.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, Mr. Crawford instructed me -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: Your instructions are what I'm giving you now.
{DIALOGUE}: Jack Crawford answers to the Director, and the Director answers to me.
{DIALOGUE}: My God, Crawford's losing it...!
{DIALOGUE}: He shouldn't even be on this, with his wife sick as she is... How the hell did you get in here, anyway?
{DIALOGUE}: He gave you - what?
{DIALOGUE}: Some kind of special ID?
{DIALOGUE}: Let's have it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (stubbornly)
{DIALOGUE}: I need the ID to fly with my gun.
{DIALOGUE}: The gun belongs in Quantico.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: Gun.
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus.
{DIALOGUE}: Turn in the ID as soon as you get back.
{DIALOGUE}: The gun, too.
{DIALOGUE}: Be on the next plane, Starling, there's one in 90 minutes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice, burning, starts for the door, then turns back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Krendler... Dr. Lecter trusts me.
{DIALOGUE}: Or at least, he used to.
{DIALOGUE}: If I could just -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: Lecter has already named Buffalo Bill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice reacts, surprised.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Krendler takes a folded computer sheet from his pocket, shoves it at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes it, reads.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: He gave us a perfectly good description, and we're on it now, so we won't be needing your little novelty act any longer - or his, either.
{DIALOGUE}: He's under close guard at the courthouse, pending a prison transfer.
{DIALOGUE}: The next plane, Officer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, doesn't this "William Rubin" strike you as - I don't know - kind of vague?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Krendler moves in very close to her, pale with anger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: Do you need a police escort, Starling?
{DIALOGUE}: Or do you think you can find the airport by yourself?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes sir.
{DIALOGUE}: I can find it by myself.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SHELBY COUNTY COURTHOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The old courthouse is a massive Gothic stronghold, with an armada of police cruisers parked at the curb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice climbs from her rented car, SLAMMING the door angrily.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Holding a rolled-up pile of papers - Dr. Lecter's drawings - she starts determinedly up the steps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A nearby commotion makes her pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Frederick Chilton in a sea of interviewers and mini-cams, is preening grandly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice carefully avoiding his gaze, slips up the steps and inside.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COURTHOUSE - GROUND FLOOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SGT. TATE, a Memphis policeman, is studying Clarice's ID.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up at her from his command desk, a bit doubtfully.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: Are you with Mr. Krendler's people?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I just left him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: Access to Lecter is strictly limited.
{DIALOGUE}: We've been getting death threats.
{META_DATA}: (hesitates again)
{DIALOGUE}: Log in, and check your weapon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up a phone, murmurs into it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he does so, Clarice glances around this main ground floor lobby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The building looks like an armed fort.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cops with shotguns guard the front door, both ends of the hall, the foot of the stairs, the single elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More of them are coming and going.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MURRAY (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Shoot, we haven't had this kinda security since the President came through town...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ELEVATOR - MOVING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice and OFFICER MURRAY, a young patrolman, ride up in an old-fashioned, CREAKING, metal-cage elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is excited.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MURRAY
{DIALOGUE}: Every cop in Tennessee wants a look at this guy.
{DIALOGUE}: 'Sit true what they're sayin' - he's some kinda vampire?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't have a name for what he is.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HISTORICAL SOCIETY ROOM - 5TH FLOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry, at a desk by the door, looks up from examining the unrolled pile of Dr. Lecter's drawings.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PEMBRY
{DIALOGUE}: You know the rules, ma'am?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, Officer Pembry.
{DIALOGUE}: I've questioned him before.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He waves her on her way, but retains the drawings for now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - WITH CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she crosses the big, spare, white octagonal room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A massive, temporary iron cage has been installed; Officer Boyle sits facing its barred door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rises, nods, moving away to allow her privacy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSIDE THE CAGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a cot and a small table, each bolted to the floor, and a flimsy paper screen, hiding a toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter sits at the table, his back to her, studying the Buffalo Bill case file.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He now wears a green prison jumpsuit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small cassette player is chained to the steel table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{META_DATA}: (without turning)
{DIALOGUE}: Good afternoon, Clarice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stops at a striped police barricade, before his bars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you might want your drawings back... Just until you get your view.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: How very thoughtful... Or did Crawford send you here for one last wheedle - before you're both booted off the case?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody sent me.
{DIALOGUE}: I came on my own.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He spins in his swivel chair, stops neatly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A coy smile.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: People will say we're in love.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Pity you tried to fool me, isn't it?
{DIALOGUE}: Pity for poor Catherine.
{DIALOGUE}: Tick-tock...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He spins again in his chair, playfully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - FAVORING CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she circles the cage, trying to keep his face in sight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Lecter, you find out everything.
{DIALOGUE}: You couldn't have talked with this "William Rubin", even once, and come out knowing so little about him... You made him up, didn't you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice... you're hardly in a position to accuse me of lying.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I think you were telling me the truth in Baltimore - or starting to.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me the rest now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: I've studied the case file, have you...?
{DIALOGUE}: Everything you need to find him is right in these pages.
{DIALOGUE}: Whatever his name is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Then tell me how.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: First principles, Clarice.
{DIALOGUE}: Simplicity.
{DIALOGUE}: Read Marcus Aurelius.
{DIALOGUE}: Of each particular thing, ask: What is it, in itself, what is its nature...?
{DIALOGUE}: What does he do, this man you seek?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: He kills w-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{META_DATA}: (sharply, as he stops)
{DIALOGUE}: No!
{DIALOGUE}: That's incidental.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ANGLE - TWO SHOT as he rises, pained by her ignorance, and crosses to the bars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: What is the first and principal thing he does, what need does he serve by killing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Anger, social resentment, sexual frus-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: No, he covets.
{DIALOGUE}: That's his nature.
{DIALOGUE}: And how do we begin to covet, Clarice?
{DIALOGUE}: Do we seek out things to covet?
{DIALOGUE}: Make an effort to answer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: We just -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: Precisely.
{DIALOGUE}: We begin by coveting what we see every day.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you feel eyes moving over your body, Clarice?
{DIALOGUE}: I hardly see how you couldn't.
{DIALOGUE}: And don't your eyes move over the things you want?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: All right, then tell me how -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: It's your turn to tell me, Clarice.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't have any more vacations to sell, on Anthrax Island.
{DIALOGUE}: Why did you run away from that ranch?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Lecter, when there's time I'll -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: We don't reckon time the same way, Clarice.
{DIALOGUE}: This is all the time you'll ever have.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Later, listen, I'll -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: I'll listen now.
{DIALOGUE}: After your father's murder, you were orphaned.
{DIALOGUE}: You were ten years old.
{DIALOGUE}: You went to live with cousins, on a sheep and horse ranch in Montana.
{DIALOGUE}: And - ?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: And - one morning I just - ran away...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns from him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He presses closer, gripping the bars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Not "just," Clarice.
{DIALOGUE}: What set you off?
{DIALOGUE}: You started what time?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Early.
{DIALOGUE}: Still dark.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Then something woke you.
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{DIALOGUE}: Did you dream...?
{DIALOGUE}: What was it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN FLASHBACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 10-year old Clarice sits up abruptly in her bed, frightened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is in a Montana ranch house; it almost dawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strange, fearful shadows on her ceiling and walls... a window, partly fogged by the cold; eerie brightness outside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I heard a strange sound...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What was it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE CHILD RISES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: crosses to the window in her nightgown, rubs the glass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't know.
{DIALOGUE}: I went to look...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH ANGLES (2ND STORY) - THE CHILD'S POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shadowy men, ranch hands, are moving in and out of a nearby barn, carrying mysterious bundles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mens' breath is steaming... A refrigerated truck idles nearby, its engine adding more steam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A strange, almost surrealistic scene...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Screaming!
{DIALOGUE}: Some kind of - screaming.
{DIALOGUE}: Like a child's voice...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE LITTLE GIRL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is terrified; she covers her ears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What did you do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Got dressed without turning on the light.
{DIALOGUE}: I went downstairs... outside...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE LITTLE GIRL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: in her winter coat, slips noiselessly towards the open barn door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She ducks into the shadows to avoid a ranch hand, who passes her with a squirming bundle of some kind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes into the barn, and she edges after him reluctantly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I crept up to the barn... I was so scared to look inside - but I had to...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE LITTLE GIRL'S POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as the open doorway LOOMS CLOSER... Bright lights inside, straw bales, the edges of stalls, then moving figures...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And what did you see, Clarice?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SQUIRMING LAMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is held down on a table by two ranch hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Lambs.
{DIALOGUE}: The lambs were screaming...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A third cowboy stretches out the lamb's neck, raises a bloody knife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just as he's about to slice its throat -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BACK TO THE ADULT CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: staring into the distance, shaken, still trembling from the child's shock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see Dr. Lecter, over her shoulder, studying her intently.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: They were slaughtering the spring lambs?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes...!
{DIALOGUE}: They were screaming.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: So you ran away...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: First I tried to free them... I opened the gate of their pen - but they wouldn't run.
{DIALOGUE}: They just stood there, confused.
{DIALOGUE}: They wouldn't run...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: But you could.
{DIALOGUE}: You did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I took one lamb.
{DIALOGUE}: And I ran away, as fast as I could...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN FLASHBACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a vast Montana plain, and crossing this, a tiny figure - the little Clarice, holding a lamb in her arms.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Where were you going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: I had no food or water.
{DIALOGUE}: It was very cold.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought - if I can even save just one... but he got so heavy.
{DIALOGUE}: So heavy...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tiny figure stops, and after a few moments sinks to the ground, hunched over in dispair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't get more than a few miles before the sheriff's car found me.
{DIALOGUE}: The rancher was so angry he sent me to live at the Lutheran orphanage in Bozeman.
{DIALOGUE}: I never saw the ranch again...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: But what became of your lamb?
{META_DATA}: (no response)
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BACK TO SCENE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as the adult Clarice turns, staring into his feverish eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She shakes her head, unwilling - or unable - to say more.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: You still wake up sometimes, don't you?
{DIALOGUE}: Wake up in the dark, with the lambs screaming?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Do you think if you saved Catherine, you could make them stop...?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you think, if Catherine lives, you won't wake up in the dark, ever again, to the screaming of the lambs?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you...?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know...!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{META_DATA}: (a pause; then, oddly at peace)
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, Clarice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (a whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me his name, Dr. Lecter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Chilton... I believe you know each other?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEW ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Clarice turns, startled, and the fuming Chilton seizes her elbow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry and Boyle are beside him, looking grim.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHILTON
{DIALOGUE}: Out.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PEMBRY
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry, ma'a m - we've got orders to have you put on a place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice struggles, pulling free of them for a moment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Brave Clarice.
{DIALOGUE}: Will you let me know if ever the lambs stop screaming?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (moving closer to the bars)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll tell you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Promise...?
{META_DATA}: (she nods. He smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: Then why not take your case file?
{DIALOGUE}: I won't be needing it anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds out the file, arm extended between the bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hesitates, then reaches to take it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VERY CLOSE ANGLE - SLOW MOTION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as the exchange is made, his index finger touches her hand, and lingers there, just for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DR. LECTER'S EYES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: widen, crackling at this touch, like sparks in a cave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Good-bye, Clarice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: hugging the case file to her chest, stares back at him as the men crowd in on her, pushing her away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER POV - MOVING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Dr. Lecter, head cocked in a smile, slowly recedes...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GARMENT SWEATSHOP - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - MR. GUMB'S POV as he pushes a rolling rack of completed leather garments, each wrapped in plastic, down as aisle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND of many sewing machines, all clattering at once, as he passes row on row of work tables.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The seamstresses, mostly black or Hispanic, glance up as he passes, then quickly avert their eyes, his presence disturbing them in some nameless way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A thin FOREMAN in a flowery shirt, sees him approaching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rises from his desk and comes over cheerfully, as the rack rolls to a stop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FOREMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, dear!
{DIALOGUE}: Punctual as always.
{DIALOGUE}: And what have you brought us today?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He seizes one of the dangling jackets, pulling up the plastic wrapper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He examines it, stroking the sleeve.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FOREMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, marvelous... You know, I always say you're the Leonardo of leather.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{META_DATA}: (a harsh whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Oil.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FOREMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Pardon...?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: You're leaving oil on the skin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The foreman quickly releases the jacket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FOREMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Of course... You'll be wanting your -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb's hand reaches INTO SHOT, snatching an envelope from him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The foreman is watching him walk away, as a seamstress comes over to take the rack of garments.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The foreman is vaguely troubled, but shakes it off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He strokes the jacket again, admiringly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FOREMAN
{META_DATA}: (to seamstress)
{DIALOGUE}: I wish we had a dozen like him...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND UPCUT - Glenn Gould playing Bach's Goldberg Variations...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MEMPHIS INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT - LOUNGE AREA - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice, in a line of other passengers, is moving slowly towards a departure ramp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through a huge plate glass window, we can see her plane.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glances back over her shoulder at
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A pair of UNIFORMED COPS brawny and impassive, their arms folded, waiting to make sure she board the flight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice sighs, turning wearily back towards the jetway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BACH CONTINUES, as we...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SHELBY CO. COURTHOUSE - HISTORICAL SOCIETY ROOM -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a steaming, rather elegant dinner tray, being carried by Pembry, as he approaches Dr. Lecter's cell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PEMBRY
{META_DATA}: (shouts)
{DIALOGUE}: Ready when you are, Doc!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE CELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the BACH is issuing from the cassette player.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beside it, on the table, the pile of Dr. Lecter's drawings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The top one is an accurate, sensitive portrait, from memory, of Clarice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beyond the table, we see Lecter's shadowy form, seated behind the paper screen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He calls out from there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Just another minute, please!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry grunts, sets the tray down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle joins him, handing him a riot baton and a Mace cannister, which Pembry fastens to belt clips.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle is similarly armed, and carries a ring of keys.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PEMBRY
{DIALOGUE}: Sumbitch demanded lamb chops for dinner, extra rare.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOYLE
{META_DATA}: (laughs)
{DIALOGUE}: What you reckon he'll want for breakfast - some fuckin' thing from the zoo?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSIDE THE SCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter sits fully clothed on the toilet - swaying slightly, eyes closed, lost in the music, tongue working in his cheek.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, like magic, a little shiny piece of metal protrudes from his lips.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He plucks it out, opens his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN EXTREME CLOSEUP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: he is holding the pocket clip from Prentice's disassembled pen - a straight, thin strip of metal, with a circular collar at one end, a square edge at the other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DR. LECTER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: lines up his thumbnail just shy of the square edge, then braces it against the stainless steel toilet rim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes down, hard, using both hands for leverage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a moment he smiles, holding up the result, and twirling it before his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN EXTREME CLOSEUP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the straight end of the clip now forms a tiny right angle, and the circular end anchors nicely between his fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OUTSIDE THE CELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry and Boyle turn as the toilet FLUSHES, and Dr. Lecter reappears, looking jaunty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PEMBRY
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, Doc, grab some floor.
{DIALOGUE}: Same drill as lunchtime.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter sits on the floor, legs straight, then wriggles backwards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stretches his arms behind him, hands and wrists through the bars, with two bars between them, and clasps his hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: I'm ready when you are, Officer Pembry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry comes around the cell to squat behind Dr. Lecter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tugs his hands farther out, rather roughly, handcuffs his wrists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shakes the cuffs, making sure of them, then nods to Boyle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEW ANGLE - AT CELL DOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Boyle picks up the dinner tray, and Pembry crosses around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry takes the keys from Boyle, unlocks the cell door, and pushes it inward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle goes inside with the tray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DR. LECTER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: watches as Boyle approaches the table, above five feet from him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle has to set his tray down on the floor to clear off some of the mess of drawings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The MUSIC plays on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VERY CLOSE ON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...Dr. Lecter's hands, outside the bars, as the makeshift key, held between the tips of his right index and middle fingers, searches for the keyhole of the cuffs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And finds it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEW ANGLE - FAVORING BOYLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he finishes clearing the drawings, then turns back towards Dr. Lecter, stooping to pick up the tray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOYLE'S RIGHT HAND
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is just inches from the tray when Dr. Lecter's hand darts INTO SHOT, snapping a handcuff onto his wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOYLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: looks up, astonished, to find himself right in the grinning face of Dr. Lecter - who just as quickly rolls sideways, and snaps -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE OTHER CUFF
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: around the bolted leg of the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And suddenly all natural SOUND and MOTION are suspended, as the MUSIC soars much louder, each separate note of it now echoing distinctly, and we see...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VARIOUS ANGLES - EACH BLURRING INTO STOP-ACTION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry starting into the cell, reaching for his riot baton...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter smashing against the cell door, driving it into Pembry, pinning him across the chest, against the door frame...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle, on one knee on the floor, digging desperately in his pants pocket for his handcuff key...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry's hand, mashed against his body by the door, as he strains frantically to reach the baton at his waist...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pembry's eyes, widening in horror as he stares at...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter's bared teeth, flashing towards him...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter gripping Pembry's face in his jaws, shaking it like a dog shakes a rat...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle finding his key, but in his terror dropping it...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter yanking the mace can and riot baton from the dazed Pembry's belt, spraying him in his bloody face, then clubbing him to his knees...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boyle, mouth open in a silent scream, finding his key again, unlocking the handcuff, but then, as he starts to rise, seeing...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter standing over him, with the riot baton raised high; he swings it viciously down, again and again and again...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then normal SOUND and MOTION are restored as we go to -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ANGLE ON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the cassette player, and the portrait of Clarice, both now flecked with blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In addition to the Bach, we now hear soft PANTING, close by, and whimpering SOBS in the background.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON DR. LECTER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: eyes closed, lost in a favorite passage of the music.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His bloody fingers drift airily with the notes, as his breathing slows to normal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens his eyes, sighs contentedly, looks down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: By the sprawled legs of Boyle lie various objects that spilled from his pants pocket - coins, a comb, a big pocketknife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DR. LECTER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: picks up the pocketknife, examines it happily.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: About a four- inch blade.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He becomes aware of the WHIMPERING, off screen, turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE ON PEMBRY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he crawls, with torturous slowness, towards the command desk, and the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is crying, but frantically determined.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PEMBRY'S POV - PARTIALLY BLURRED, THEN CLEARING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Above the desk, hanging from pegs, are his and Boyle's holstered revolvers...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COURTHOUSE - GROUND FLOOR LOBBY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bronze arrow above the elevator swings towards "5," then indicates a stop there, at the top floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FAVORING SGT. TATE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: at his command desk, as he stares at the indicator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another cop, JACOBS, sits on the desk's edge, flipping through a magazine; many more cops can be seen beyond them, idling in the lobby.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: What is this shit...?
{DIALOGUE}: Did somebody go up to five?
{META_DATA}: (Jacobs shakes his head)
{DIALOGUE}: Call Pembry, ask him what -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A GUNSHOT, and then, moments later, TWO MORE quick ones, echo down the nearby stairwell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sgt. Tate jumps to his feet, grabs a radio mike, as the other cops stir, confused and noisy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (into mike)
{DIALOGUE}: CP, shots fired on five!
{DIALOGUE}: Repeat, shots fires on five!
{DIALOGUE}: Outside posts look sharp, we've got a..
{DIALOGUE}: Ho-ly shit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE BRONZE ARROW
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: has begun to descend.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Down to 4, then past 4...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BACK ON SGT. TATE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he reacts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other cops, behind him, are now in a full uproar, shouting, pulling out guns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (to the others)
{DIALOGUE}: SHUT UP...!
{DIALOGUE}: Guard mount, double up on your outside posts.
{DIALOGUE}: Bobby, get the vests.
{DIALOGUE}: Rainey, Howard, cover that fucking elevator if it comes all the way to -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: A COP (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: It stopped!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE BRONZE ARROW
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: has, indeed, frozen at 3.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sgt. Tate lifts the microphone again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (into mike)
{DIALOGUE}: Seal off a ten-block radius.
{DIALOGUE}: Get me the SWAT team and an ambulance, double quick.
{DIALOGUE}: We're going up.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STAIRWELL - NIGHT (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH ANGLE on Sgt. Tate as he leads a five-man squad, all in bulletproof vests, up the stone stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They move fast but carefully, covering each other from landing to landing with drawn revolvers, shotguns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The distant Back MUSIC makes a ghostly echo in here...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. THIRD FLOOR CORRIDOR - NIGHT (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A thin rectangle of light on the floor from the open elevator door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We can't see inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The MUSIC sounds closer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SGT. TATE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: approaches very cautiously, gun aimed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other cops, behind him, fan out silently to set up angles of fire, checking the various office doors - all locked - as they creep up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - OVER TATE'S SHOULDER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he reaches the side of the elevator, hesitates, then spins to point his gun inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He backs away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (shouts at ceiling)
{DIALOGUE}: Pembry?
{DIALOGUE}: Boyle...?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HISTORICAL SOCIETY ROOM - NIGHT (BRIGHTLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE on the door, from inside, its lettering reversed on the frosted glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Bach is VERY LOUD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a moment the door is shouldered open, hard enough for the glass to shatter, Tate following his gun inside, moving low, then other cops appearing behind him in the doorframe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They all freeze, staring in utter horror.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: Oh no... no...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEIR POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is a brief snapshot from hell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two uniformed bodies, one sprawled on its back near the door, the other still in the cell, have been savaged by a knife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood and gore everywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The faces are unrecognizable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SGT. TATE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: struggles for control, as the other cops move grimly around him, into the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls his walkie-talkie from his belt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (into mike)
{DIALOGUE}: Command post... Two offi-
{META_DATA}: (a beat; clears his throat)
{DIALOGUE}: Two officers down.
{DIALOGUE}: Prisoner is missing.
{DIALOGUE}: Repeat, Lecter is missing... He's stripped the bed, might be making a rope, check all windows.
{DIALOGUE}: Where the fuck is my ambulance?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE CELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a cop angrily punches OFF the music.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jacobs kneels with his fingers on Boyle's neck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACOBS
{DIALOGUE}: Boyle is dead, Sarge.
{DIALOGUE}: His gun's gone...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE OTHER BODY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a cop gently removes a revolver from the bloody fist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Murray, the young patrolman, brings his ear reluctantly close to the gory face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bloody bubble appears there; the wreckage GROANS, very softly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MURRAY
{DIALOGUE}: This one's alive!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tate crosses, kneels to see for himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Murray looks green.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: Take ahold of him where he can feel your hands, son.
{DIALOGUE}: Talk to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MURRAY
{DIALOGUE}: What's his name, Sarge?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: It's Pembry, now talk to him, God dammit.
{META_DATA}: (into radio, looking around)
{DIALOGUE}: Boyle's dead, Pembry's read bad.
{DIALOGUE}: Lecter is missing and armed - he took Boyle's gun...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other cop, checking the cylinder of Pembry's gun, holds up one finger to Tate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (into radio)
{DIALOGUE}: Pembry got off one round - there's a chance Lecter was hit.
{DIALOGUE}: We heard a total of three shots fired, so he's got four left... He's got a knife, too.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET IN FRONT OF COURTHOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VARIOUS ANGLES on a floodlit scene of barely controlled pandemonium.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flashing red lights, men shouting commands, SIRENS in the distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SWAT members, in full gear, leap from a black van... fan out... swarm up the steps... EMS orderlies unload a gurney from an ambulance... Cops kneel for cover behind cars, aiming guns and rifles up at the windows...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HISTORICAL SOCIETY ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A trio of EMS orderlies work fast over the body, already strapped on its gurney.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They bandage a big plastic airway into place, over the butchered face, checking for a pulse at the neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Young Murray crouches, sickened, gripping a bloody fist.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MURRAY
{DIALOGUE}: You're just fine, Pembry, lookin' good, buddy, you're gonna make it...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One orderly massages the heart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another is popping a plasma bag, ready to insert the needle, when the body starts convulsing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ORDERLY
{DIALOGUE}: Downstairs - let's go!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quickly the gurney is elevated, wheeled out of the room, with cops rushing forward to open the doors, help push, SWAT men are running by in the hall, automatic rifles at the ready...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. THE ELEVATOR - DESCENDING - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sgt. Tate, riding down with Jacobs, has his radio out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (into mike)
{DIALOGUE}: Ten-four, Lieutenant.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm on the elevator, bringing it down.
{DIALOGUE}: Pembry and Boyle are both cleared, top three floors secured, main stairwell secured.
{DIALOGUE}: He's somewhere on -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A spot of blood falls on his cheek.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He and Jacobs stare at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another spot hits his shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEIR POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood is dripping slowly from the corner of the service hatch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sgt. Tate motions for silence, as both men draw their guns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (into mike)
{DIALOGUE}: Uh, we're pretty sure he's somewhere on two, sir... That's all for now, over.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GROUND FLOOR LOBBY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The elevator doors open, and Tate and Jacobs hurry out, stepping quickly to the side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tate reaches back in and -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Locks the elevator into position, with its doors open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OTHER COPS are rushing up to them, curious, as Tate frantically pushes them aside, gesturing for silence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: He's on the roof of the elevator!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. THIRD FLOOR CORRIDOR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two SWAT officers, PETERSON and KUBELL, turn a key, unlocking and opening this floor's elevator doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shaft is dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lying prone, they inch up to the edge, Peterson extends a mirror, on a long pole, out into the shaft.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE MIRROR (DISTORTED BY THE ANGLE)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Is a distant figure, in a green prison jumpsuit, lying on his stomach, atop the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shiny revolver is near one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PETERSON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: whispers into a radio, as Kubell carefully tips an assault rifle, with a flashlight taped to its barrel, over the edge.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PETERSON
{DIALOGUE}: I see him... There's a weapon by his hand.
{DIALOGUE}: He's not moving...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RADIO VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Can you get the drop?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PETERSON
{DIALOGUE}: We got the drop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RADIO VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: One warning.
{DIALOGUE}: Then take him out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Peterson nods to Kubell, who switches ON the flashlight, as Peterson shouts down the shaft.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PETERSON
{DIALOGUE}: Quinn!!
{DIALOGUE}: put your hands on your head!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE MIRROR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the green figure shows no movement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON THE COPS AGAIN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Peterson mutters to Kubell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PETERSON
{DIALOGUE}: Put one in his leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VERY CLOSE ON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The figure below, as Kubell's gunshot ROARS, echoing hugely in the shaft, and a slug rips through the jumpsuited leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The figure doesn't stir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PETERSON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: staring down the shaft, raises his mike again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PETERSON
{DIALOGUE}: No movement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RADIO VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, Johnny, hold your fire...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GROUND FLOOR LOBBY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small army of cops is now covering the elevator doorway, from both sides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tate crouches next to the SWAT COMMANDER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SWAT COMMANDER
{META_DATA}: (into radio mike)
{DIALOGUE}: We're coming into the car, we're opening the hatch.
{DIALOGUE}: Watch his hands.
{DIALOGUE}: Any fire will come from us.
{DIALOGUE}: Affirm?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PETERSON'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Got it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SWAT commander hands his radio to another cop, then looks at Tate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long, tense moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he waves a signal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as we follow a picked team of four SWAT cops, in full body armor, rushing into the elevator car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two men move to the corners, aim assault rifles at the ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A third man sets a stepladder in place, and the fourth man, armed with a big Colt, hurries up the ladder and unclips the hatch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...the service hatch, as the hinged cover drops open, and a body tumbles through, dangling head first, until it's caught at the waist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the back of the head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SGT. TATE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: shoulders through the SWAT cops for a closer look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns towards the SWAT commander, astonished.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. TATE
{DIALOGUE}: That's Pembry!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. EMS AMBULANCE - MOVING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the rear chamber, a young EMS ATTENDANT is braced against the vehicle's sway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him, the stretchered form of his patient, and, through a curtained opening, the driver.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND of the siren.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ATTENDANT
{META_DATA}: (into radio mike)
{DIALOGUE}: He's comatose, but his vital signs are good.
{DIALOGUE}: Pressure's 130 over 90... Yeah, 90!
{DIALOGUE}: Pulse 85...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him, in slightly BLURRED FOCUS, the bloody figure sits slowly upright...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ATTENDANT
{DIALOGUE}: His convulsions have stopped, but he's got so much loose skin on his face, it's hard to tell if -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly he stops, becoming aware of a strange HISSING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns, puzzled...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE POCKETKNIFE BLADE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: in Lecter's fist, flashes high in the air...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SIX-LANE FREEWAY - NIGHT (ARC LIGHTS)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE on the EMS ambulance, as it races along normally, its SIREN blazing, the heavy flow of traffic parting to make way for it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then suddenly it begins to weave erratically, changing lanes, before drifting dangerously to a full stop, almost side-ways.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cars swerve to avoid hitting it, HONKING angrily...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSER ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: on the stopped ambulance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a long, still moment, the wind-shield wipes come on, incongruously, then stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then the SIREN is shut OFF, and the flashers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ambulance starts rolling again - at first jerkingly, then with increasing speed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We follow it for several more moments, until is passes - and we LINGER on...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BIG GREEN INTERSTATE SIGN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...that reads "Memphis International Airport / 2 miles."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ANGLE - THROUGH AMBULANCE WINDSHIELD
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter's face is slowly REVEALED, as he wipes across it with a fistful of gauze, tossing it aside...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MONTANA PLAIN - DUSK - (IN FLASHBACK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE, rushing with dizzy swiftness over the prairie, over waving grasses... a long passage... before we come at last to the girl Clarice, sitting with her lamb, hunched in despair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She rises, her face tear-stained, and turns from us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Holding the lamb, she starts back the way she came...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COUNTRY DIRT ROAD - NIGHT - BRIGHT MOONLIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE, very rapid, down this road... coming at last to a stopped highway patrol car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice, with her lamb, is standing in the car's headlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She starts wearily towards the sheriff...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RANCH BARNYARD - NEAR DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRANE ANGLE - sweeping rapidly DOWN into the barnyard towards the arriving highway patrol car, as it stops... RUSHING to the little girl as she steps from the car, holding the lamb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dark figure of the rancher ENTERS FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he roughly takes the lamb from her, we HOLD on a CLOSEUP of her face - stunned, blank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She EXITS FRAME...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BARN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - CLARICE'S POV as she walks towards the open barn doorway... It looms CLOSER... The rancher is revealed, a shadowy figure, pinning the lamb on the killing table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His knife hand sweeps up high, then holds... He turns TO CAMERA, his face breaking into the light - and it is the face of Dr. Lecter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles his terrible smile at the young Clarice...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FBI DORM - PAY PHONE IN HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - coming in very CLOSE on the adult Clarice's face - shocked, devastated - as she stands alone by the dangling receiver...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SHOWER STALL - FBI DORM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a shower head, as water suddenly blasts out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice moves INTO SHOT, as she scrubs her face and hair compulsively, almost desperately, unable to get clean...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: They found the ambulance...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLARICE'S DORM ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice is hunched on her cot, in a bathrobe, her hair wet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Buffalo Bill case file, a thick bundle, rests by her feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia hovers anxiously nearby.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: In the parking garage at Memphis airport.
{DIALOGUE}: The crew was dead.
{DIALOGUE}: He killed a tourist, too.
{DIALOGUE}: Got his clothes, cash... By now he could be anywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes are red-rimmed with exhaustion, and something close to despair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reads Ardelia's thought.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: He won't come after me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: Why not?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (bitterly)
{DIALOGUE}: It would be rude.
{DIALOGUE}: And he wouldn't get to ask any more questions...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia sits beside her, touches her arm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice - you did the best anybody could have for Catherine Martin.
{DIALOGUE}: You stuck your neck out for her and you got your butt kicked for her and you tried.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not your fault it ended this way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: The worst part - the thing that's making me crazy - is that Bill is right in front of me.
{DIALOGUE}: Only I can't see him...
{META_DATA}: (touching the case file)
{DIALOGUE}: Lecter said, everything I need to catch him is right here, in these pages...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: Lecter said a lot of things.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (shakes her head)
{DIALOGUE}: He's here, Ardelia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia stares back at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND UPCUT - the low throb of a washing machine...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAUNDRY ROOM - ACADEMY DORM - NIGHT (VERY LATE)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice has spread out the case file across two washing machines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia, cross-legged on a dryer, studies another pile of forms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nearby is their laundry basket, detergent box.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{META_DATA}: (surprised)
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, is this Lecter's handwriting?
{DIALOGUE}: She holds up the map, with its location markings for the kidnapping and body dump sites.
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice takes it, looks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT - THE MAP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: with newly inked words in Dr. Lecter's precise, elegant hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice, doesn't this random scattering of sites seem overdone to you?
{DIALOGUE}: Doesn't it seem desperately random - like the elaborations of a bad liar?
{DIALOGUE}: Ta... Hannibal Lecter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NEW ANGLE - TWO SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Clarice looks up at Ardelia, puzzled but excited.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: "Desperately random."
{DIALOGUE}: What does he mean?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: Not random at all, maybe.
{DIALOGUE}: Like there's some pattern here...?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: But there is no pattern.
{DIALOGUE}: There's no connection at all among these places, or the computers would've nailed it!
{DIALOGUE}: They're even found in random order.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: Well, except for the one girl.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: What girl?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: The one that was weighted down.
{DIALOGUE}: Where is she...?
{DIALOGUE}: Fred something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They search among the inserts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice finds the graduation photo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Fredrica Bimmel, from Belvedere, Ohio.
{DIALOGUE}: The first girl taken, but the third body found... Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: 'Cause she didn't drift.
{DIALOGUE}: He weighted her down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: But why?
{DIALOGUE}: He didn't weight the others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice moves, on fire, unable to keep still.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: The first, what the hell did Lecter say about... "First principles," he said.
{DIALOGUE}: Simplicity... What does this guy do, he "covets."
{DIALOGUE}: How do we first start to covet?
{DIALOGUE}: "We covet what we see -"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stops, turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She grabs the photo of Fredrica from Ardelia, stares at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up, trembling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: "- every day."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: Hot damn, Clarice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: He knew her...!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FBI BUILDING - OFFICE OF THE DIRECTOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice and Crawford are seated in front of Director Burke, who's at his desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another chair is empty, because Krendler is pacing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All four are nearing their boiling points.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe he lives in this, this Belvedere, Ohio, too!
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe he saw her every day, and killed her sort of spontaneously.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe he just meant to... give her a 7-Up and talk about the choir.
{DIALOGUE}: But then -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: Starling -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: But then he had to cover up, make her seem just like all the rest of them.
{DIALOGUE}: That's what Lecter was hinting!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: The market in Lecter hints is way down, today, okay?
{DIALOGUE}: I've got two good men dead in Memphis, and three civilians.
{DIALOGUE}: I've got -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Who the hell's fault is -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: - a U.S. Senator who's half out of her head because her daughter's going to be murdered today!
{DIALOGUE}: And all because of your mind games with fucking Lecter!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: If you hadn't interfered, he'd still be in custody in Baltimore!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURKE
{DIALOGUE}: Jack -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KRENDLER
{DIALOGUE}: You sent in a green recruit, with a phony goddamn offer -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: You're just trying to cover your ass for letting him escape!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURKE
{DIALOGUE}: THAT'S ENOUGH!
{DIALOGUE}: All of you...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long silence, as they all struggle to regain composure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crawford, who was at the point of striking Krendler, finally retakes his seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burke looks sadly at Crawford and Clarice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURKE
{META_DATA}: (very reluctantly)
{DIALOGUE}: Starling, I'm afraid I have no choice.
{DIALOGUE}: You're suspended from the Academy.
{META_DATA}: (Crawford starts to interrupt)
{DIALOGUE}: Not another word!
{META_DATA}: (to Clarice)
{DIALOGUE}: This is pending a reevaluation of your fitness for the service.
{DIALOGUE}: I promise you'll get a fair hearing.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Jack... you're ordered to take compassionate leave.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll spend the rest of the day briefing the AG's office, then transfer command of the task force, effective by 1800 hours.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, Jack... Go home.
{DIALOGUE}: Take care of Bella.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice and Crawford stare back at him, drained.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long and very painful silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not even Krendler looks happy.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SIDEWALK OUTSIDE FBI BUILDING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice and Crawford walk out slowly, stand there a moment, not knowing what to say, not wanting to face each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: All his victims are women... His obsession is women, he lives to hunt women.
{DIALOGUE}: But not one women is hunting him - except me.
{DIALOGUE}: I can walk in a woman's room and know three times as much about her as a man would.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I have to go to Belvedere.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: You heard them.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't have that authority anymore.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: You do until six p.m.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares at her sadly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks, for the first time, defeated, old beyond his years.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Ohio is cold ground.
{DIALOGUE}: Picked over, ten months ago.
{DIALOGUE}: Our people worked it, so did the locals.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: But not from this angle.
{DIALOGUE}: Not thinking he knew her.
{DIALOGUE}: You've got to send me!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Bureau for 28 years, Starling.
{DIALOGUE}: I won't disobey orders, not even now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: But I just became a private citizen.
{DIALOGUE}: I can go anywhere I want to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: With ID and a gun...?
{DIALOGUE}: Impersonating a federal agent is a felony.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: He's going to kill her, Mr. Crawford.
{DIALOGUE}: This morning, or maybe at noon, but today, and Belvedere's our last chance.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm flying there, right now, unless you stop me.
{DIALOGUE}: You want my ID?
{DIALOGUE}: Here - take it...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares at her, a long moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catherine's life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice's passion, and future.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His loyalty to the Bureau.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Call it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{META_DATA}: (pulls out his wallet)
{DIALOGUE}: There's about $300 here... And a hotline code number.
{DIALOGUE}: They'll patch you through to me, wherever I am.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She raises her hand to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She wants to touch him face, or his neck, but can't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally she takes his money and card.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He watches, frightened for both of them, as she backs away, smiles, then turns, racing towards the surveillance van.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND UPCUT - the scratchy recording of Fats Waller SINGING, as we...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY (DIM LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON the needle of the Victrola, on the spinning record, as Mr. Gumb's fingers lift away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MUSIC continues in background.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{META_DATA}: (calling out)
{DIALOGUE}: Preeeeecious...!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON the moth cage, as Mr. Gumb's fingers search through the humus, and find a plump new cocoon, lifting it out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door of the cage is left open, and one or two of the adult moths flutter out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Precious, come on Precious!
{DIALOGUE}: Busy busy day today...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a clean towel, beside the sink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cocoon is gently placed in readiness alongside four shiny skinning knives.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Momma's gonna be sooo beautiful!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a stainless steel Colt Python, with a six-inch barrel, as the cylinder is spun, and the hammer gets a practice cock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The metallic CLICK is deep and loud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A note of alarm has entered Mr. Gumb's voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: You come here this minute, you little scamp!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE on Mr. Gumb, wearing the kimono, as he walks through his sewing workroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His back is to us; he is looking anxiously under the furniture.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops, straightens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Genuinely scared.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Precious...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE - OVER THE PIT OPENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Towards Mr. Gumb, as he stops at one of the doorways of the oubliette chamber.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares inside; his face in shadows.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Sweetheart...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From the distant bottom of the pit, we hear Catherine's voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: She'd down here you sack of shit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb's fist flies to his mouth, and he sags against the doorframe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A little groan escaped him; the dog answers with a series of YIPS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UPWARD ANGLE, FROM THE PIT BOTTOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Mr. Gumb's dark shape leans cautiously over the edge.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Precious, are you all right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: REVERSE ANGLE ON CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: crouched to one side, clutching the dog to her chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seeing Mr. Gumb, the dog squirms frantically, BARKING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Get me a telephone.
{DIALOGUE}: Lower it down to me.
{DIALOGUE}: Do it now, mister!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to have to hurt this little dog.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UPWARD ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: on Mr. Gumb, as, with a cry of fury, he whips the Colt from inside his kimono.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The muzzle gleams as he takes aim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catherine yanks the dog up, into his line of fire, screaming at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: You shoot motherfucker you better kill me quick or I'll break her fucking neck, I swear to God!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{META_DATA}: (wails)
{DIALOGUE}: Nooooooo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tucking the dog under one arm, she grabs its muzzle, twisting the head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dog WHINES piteously.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Back off, you son of a bitch!
{DIALOGUE}: Back off!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UPWARD ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Mr. Gumb cries out again - a terrible, inarticulate scream of rage and anguish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But then he slowly lowers his gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: REVERSE ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On Catherine, as she maintains her grip.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: That's better... Now get me a live telephone.
{DIALOGUE}: Get a long extension and lower is down here... And you better do it fast, too, 'cause I think her leg's broken.
{DIALOGUE}: She's in pain, mister, she needs a vet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: stares down at her, a long beat, breathing heavily.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: You think she's in pain?
{DIALOGUE}: You don't know what pain is.
{DIALOGUE}: But you're going to find out...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And abruptly he vanishes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND of his footsteps, rushing off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CATHERINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: begins shaking, hands and arms twitching uncontrollably.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hugs the little dog tight to her chest, buries her face in its fur, sobbing...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RESIDENTIAL STREET - BELVEDERE, OHIO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH ANGLE as a rented sedan pulls up to the curb, stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a moment Clarice climbs out, a bit stiffly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Double- checking this address, she glances up from a folded street map to -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN OLD, THREE-STORY WOODEN HOUSE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: in a row of similarly shabby homes, all backing onto a narrow river.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A path of boards, laid over mud, leads back along this house towards the brown water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND of hammering from there.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BIMMEL HOUSE - BACK YARD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An awesome huddle of pigeon coops sprawls by the brackish water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The birds' COOING mixes with the HAMMERING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tall, gaunt man in a knit cap is obsessively pounding nails into a new coop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: approaches him, and the man lowers his hammer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has red- rimmed eyes of watery blue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face is deeply seamed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Bimmel...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares back at her, warily.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BIMMEL HOUSE - STAIRCASE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH ANGLE - LOOKING DOWN as Mr. Bimmel leads Clarice up a steep flight of steps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bannister is worn, sags a bit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. BIMMEL
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know nothin' new to tell ya.
{DIALOGUE}: The police been back here so many times already... Fredrica went into Columbus on the bus to see about a job.
{DIALOGUE}: She left the interview OK.
{DIALOGUE}: She never come home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice pauses, at the landing, to look at a framed photo: the familiar graduation portrait.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Others pictures show Fredrica as a young girl, toddler, infant - plump and hopeful at each age.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. BIMMEL
{DIALOGUE}: Her room's how she left it.
{DIALOGUE}: Just shut the door when you're done.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FREDRICA'S BEDROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE'S POV - MOVING SLOWLY as she takes in flowery chintz curtains... posters of Madonna and Blondie... a twin bed, with worn, stuffed animals on the pillow... a big sewing machine in the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: turns, absorbing nuances.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is loneliness here, an echo of desperation under this steeply pitches ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shrill MEOW, and she looks down...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BIG TORTOISESHELL CAT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is rubbing against her ankles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: picks up the cat, scratches behind his ears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glances up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN A FULL-LENGTH MIRROR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: she and the cat stares back at their own reflection...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sitting at the desk, turns the pages of a high school yearbook.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cat is curled on her lap...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: kneeling by the old Decca record player, flips through LPs and singles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cat has wandered off...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: pulling a string to light up the closet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is surprised and intrigued to see an extensive wardrobe, groaning from the rod.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shelf above the rod is stacked high with sewing supplies, in clear plexiboxes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She flips through the hanging clothes, pulls out one dress, on its hanger, for a closer look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE DRESS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is very big, to fit Fredrica, but beautifully cut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some of the seams still look unfinished.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns it around, sees a blue tissue dressmaker's pattern still pinned to the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FAVORING THE SEWING MACHINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Clarice turns, looks towards it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hangs the dress on the closet door knob, crosses to sit at the machine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes off its dust cover.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She runs one hand over the cool metal, as a taunting memory forms in her mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Billy wants to change, too, Clarice.
{DIALOGUE}: But there's the problem of his size, you see...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns, looks again at the unfinished dress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly she straightens, her attention riveted by something...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE'S POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the printed pattern, down at the lower back of the outlined dress, are two bold black triangles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We RUSH CLOSER to there shapes, before jumping back to -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: who stares at them, starting to tremble.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Even if he were a woman, he'd have to be a big one...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN FLASHBACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: those missing triangles of skin on the dead girl's back, in the funeral home in West Virginia...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she jumps to her feet, with a fierce joy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Sewing darts.
{DIALOGUE}: You bastard.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BIMMEL PARLOR - DOWNSTAIRS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice paces, in an exuberant rush, amidst the worn furniture.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: He's making himself a "woman suit," Mr. Crawford - out of real women!
{DIALOGUE}: And he can sew, this guy, he's really skilled.
{DIALOGUE}: A dressmaker, or a tailor -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Starling -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: That's why they're all so big - because he needs a lot of skin!
{DIALOGUE}: He keeps them alive to starve them awhile - to loosen their skin, so that -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Starling, we know who he is!
{DIALOGUE}: And where he is.
{DIALOGUE}: We're on our way now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (pause; surprised)
{DIALOGUE}: Where?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FBI TURBOJET - FLYING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crawford sits at a communications console, with Burroughs, in headphones, by his side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This forward section of the cabin is crammed with hi-tech equipment, all lit up and WHIRRING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through a window we see clouds, part of the jet's wing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{META_DATA}: (into speaker phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Calumet City, edge of Chicago.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be on the ground in 45 minutes with the Hostage Rescue Team.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm back in charge, Starling.
{DIALOGUE}: He's mine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INTERCUTTING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Clarice reacts; her happiness for Crawford is tinged with disappointment at being so suddenly out of the hunt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (on phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, that's great news.
{DIALOGUE}: But how -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Johns Hopkins finally came up with a name for us.
{DIALOGUE}: We fed him into Known Offenders, and he came up cherries.
{META_DATA}: (takes a paper from Burroughs)
{DIALOGUE}: Subject's name is "Jamie Gumb," AKA "John Grant."
{DIALOGUE}: Lecter's description was accurate, he just lied about the name.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSIDE THE JET - MOVING ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: from the rear of the cabin forward, as we slowly PASS the twelve-man HRT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're seated in full gear, hardshell armor, quietly checking and rechecking their bulging cases of weapons - silencer automatics, shotguns, stun grenades...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: This Gumb's a real beauty.
{DIALOGUE}: Slaughtered both his grandparents when he was twelve, and did nine years in juvenile psychiatric.
{DIALOGUE}: Where, Starling, he took vocational rehab, and learned a useful trade...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INTERCUTTING
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Sewing...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Take a bow.
{DIALOGUE}: Customs had some paper on his alias.
{DIALOGUE}: They stopped a carton two years ago at LAX - live caterpillars from Surinam.
{DIALOGUE}: The addressee was "John Grant."
{DIALOGUE}: Calumet Power & Light's given us two possible residences under that alias.
{DIALOGUE}: We're hitting one, Chicago SWAT's taking the other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (eagerly)
{DIALOGUE}: Chicago's only about 400 miles from here.
{DIALOGUE}: I could be there in -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: No, Starling, there isn't time.
{DIALOGUE}: And you've still got crucial work to do in Ohio.
{DIALOGUE}: We want him for murder, not kidnapping.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm counting on you to link him to the Bimmel girl, before he's indicted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice tries hard to swallow her disappointment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes sir... I'll do my best.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{META_DATA}: (pause; gently)
{DIALOGUE}: Starling - you've earned back your place in the Academy.
{DIALOGUE}: We never would've found him without you, and nobody's ever going to forget that.
{DIALOGUE}: Least of all me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Yes sir.
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, sir...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRAWFORD
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: switches off, feeling bad for her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the console near him, the fax machine starts to CHATTER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns, looks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURROUGHS (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Here he comes, Jack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: an emerging sheet, as Gumb's face is printed out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see just his hair, then the top of his forehead, before we...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BIMMEL BACK YARD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice walks slowly across the yard, absorbing all this news, before suddenly leaping into the air and pumping her fist in triumph, with a happy yelp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then she sees -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. BIMMEL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: staring at her in surprise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits by his coops, smoking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: somewhat embarrassed, crosses over to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Bimmel... did Fredrica ever mention a man named Jamie Gumb, from Calumet City?
{DIALOGUE}: Or John Grant?
{META_DATA}: (he shakes his head)
{DIALOGUE}: Did she know any men that sew?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. BIMMEL
{DIALOGUE}: She sewed for everybody.
{DIALOGUE}: Stores, ladies, whatever.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know about men.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Who was her best friend, Mr. Bimmel?
{DIALOGUE}: Who'd she hang out with?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. AN ISOLATED RUNWAY - O'HARE AIRPORT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The FBI turbojet is parked, its gangway down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crawford, Burroughs, and the HRT squad, carrying their bags of weapons, CLATTER rapidly down the metal steps...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Freaked me out.
{DIALOGUE}: Get your skin peeled off, is that a bummer...?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SAVING & LOAN - BELVEDERE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STACY HUBKA - short, perky, early 20's - sits nervously at her desk, talking to Clarice, who jots in her notebook.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the background.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: beyond them, bank tellers, lines of waiting customers, MUZAK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{DIALOGUE}: They said she was just rags, like somebody -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Stacy, did Fredrica ever mention a man named Jamie Gumb?
{DIALOGUE}: Or John Grant?
{META_DATA}: (Stacy shakes her head)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you think she could've had a friend you didn't know about?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{DIALOGUE}: No way.
{DIALOGUE}: She had a guy, I'da known, believe me.
{DIALOGUE}: Sewing was her life, she was really great at it.
{DIALOGUE}: Poor Freddie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Did you ever work with her?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{DIALOGUE}: Oh sure, me'n Pam Malavesi used to help her do alterations for old Mrs. Lippman.
{DIALOGUE}: Lots of people worked for her, she had the business from all these retail stores?
{DIALOGUE}: But she was like, totally old, it was more'n she could handle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Where does Mrs. Lippman live?
{DIALOGUE}: I'd like to talk to her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{DIALOGUE}: She died.
{DIALOGUE}: She went to Florida to retire, like two years ago?
{DIALOGUE}: She dies own there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice reacts, disappointed at the ending of this trail.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{META_DATA}: (beat; shyly)
{DIALOGUE}: Is that a pretty good job, FBI agent?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I think so.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{DIALOGUE}: You get to travel around and stuff?
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, better places then this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes you do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STACY
{DIALOGUE}: Freddie was so happy for me when I got this job.
{DIALOGUE}: This - toaster giveaways, and Barry Manilow on the speakers all day - she thought this was really hot shit.
{DIALOGUE}: What did she know, big dummy...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly she's fighting tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice reaches to hug her.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RESIDENTIAL STREET - CALUMET CITY, ILLINOIS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ANGLE on what appears to be, at first, a calm, ordinary neighborhood of working class two- and three-story houses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But the street is strangely quiet, deserted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a few moments, we become aware of movement - armed, dark-clad figures creeping swiftly and in silence from shrubs to garage corners, from parked cars to porches, appearing and then disappearing...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY (DIM LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON Mr. Gumb, as he settles a big pair of infra-red night-vision goggles over his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moths flutter past his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His mouth is set in a grim line...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET IN CALUMET CITY - FRONT YARD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An HRT cop, prone beneath a hedge, is joined by a 2nd HRT Cop, who throws himself to the grass beside him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They both take aim with their scoped rifles at -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TELEPHOTO ANGLE (WITH RIFLE CROSSHAIRS)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front door of a big, nearby, split-level house...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY (DIM LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a fuse box, as Mr. Gumb reaches in, flips a switch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lights go out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND of a second switch, and the cellar is bathed in a green glow...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET IN CALUMET CITY - NEIGHBOR'S HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A little boy, riding his tricycle in his driveway, is suddenly startled to find himself staring into the grim face of -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MEMBER OF THE HRT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: crouched by his garage, armed to the teeth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the little boy starts to cry, the cop pulls him into the shadows, covering his mouth.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY (GREEN LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb, in his kimono and goggles, creeps silently through his workrooms - knees bent, painted toes places ever so delicately, the Colt held aloft - as more moths flutter past him in the eerie light...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET IN CALUMENT CITY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A florist's van turns the corner, comes slowly down the street and stops at the curb in front of the split-level.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The driver, in a gray deliveryman's uniform and cap, climbs out of the cab, walks briskly to the panel door, on the street side of the van, and slides it open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans in, comes out with a long, thin red-ribboned floral box, starts calmly towards the house...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY (GREEN LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB'S POV - MOVING ANGLE on the top of the oubliette, a glowing green circle in the dark, as it draws closer and closer... and then Catherine comes INTO VIEW, at the bottom of the pit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is crouched, exhausted, staring straight up at him - but she can't see him in this infra-red darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Precious is curled into her stomach, asleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The futon is up to Catherine's waist, but there's a clear shot at her head and neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking down at her, smiles...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET IN CALUMET CITY - SUSPECT'S HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE on the "deliveryman," seen from behind, as he mounts three steps to the split-level's front porch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tucked into the small of his back if a 9 mm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: automatic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRAWFORD AND BURROUGHS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: have slipped out of the van, and are crouched behind it now, with drawn guns, watching tensely as -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE "DELIVERYMAN"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: settles the floral box in the crook of his left arm, reaches out with his right hand towards the buzzer...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY (GREEN LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly, savoring the moment, Mr. Gumb aims the big Colt, which is already cocked, using both hands... He is just about to squeeze the trigger, when we hear his DOOR BUZZER, surprisingly loud and close by.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns, startled, and sees -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DUSTY BLACK METAL BOX
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the extension buzzer, mounted high on the wall, which is making the hideous, grating JANGLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It finally stops, but not before waking Precious, who starts frantically BARKING, off screen, as -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: raises his gun again, spinning back towards -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS POV - THE PIT BOTTOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: where Catherine, hearing but still not seeing him, quickly yanks the futon over both herself and the dog.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Instantly the two of them become one squirming, indistinguishable mass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: bites his lip, his aim wavering, as he can't decide where to safely place his shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The maddening BUZZER sounds again, even more insistently, and he cries out with frustration and fury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But as the BUZZER continues, he reluctantly uncocks his gun, looking up angrily towards his front door...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S FRONT DOOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door opens, on a chain, and Clarice peers in, smiling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Good afternoon... I wonder if you could help me.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm looking for Mrs. Lippman's family?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb frowns out at Clarice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: For the first time ever, we get a well-lit view of his bland, pale-eyed moon of a face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: They don't live here anymore.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FRONT DOOR OF SUSPECT'S HOUSE - CALUMET CITY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The "deliveryman" yanks a 12 lb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sledgehammer from the floral box, swings it with all his might against the door knob, blowing it through as -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crawford and Burroughs race towards the door, guns up...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MR. GUMB'S FRONT DOOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb starts to close the door, only to have Clarice push back against it, politely but firmly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She holds up her ID.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me, but I really do need to talk to you.
{DIALOGUE}: This was Mrs. Lippman's house.
{DIALOGUE}: Did you know her?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Just briefly.
{DIALOGUE}: What's the problem, Officer?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SUSPECT'S HOUSE - CALUMENT CITY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bedroom window disintegrates as a flash grenade is shot through it, EXPLODING on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An instant later, a black- clad HRT cop dives through the shattered glass, rolls across the floor, comes up on one knee swiveling his sawed-off shotgun...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MR. GUMB'S FRONT DOOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice and Mr. Gumb, still eyeing each other through the door crack...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm investigating the death of Fredrica Bimmel.
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you, please?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Jack Gordon.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Gordon, did you know Fredrica when she worked for Mrs. Lippman?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: Wait... Was she a great, fat person?
{DIALOGUE}: I may have seen her, I'm not sure...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SUSPECT'S HOUSE - CALUMET CITY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE as Burroughs moves quickly down a hallway and enters the living room, where Crawford is standing, with his gun held down by his side, surrounded by several other cops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burroughs shakes his head: Nothing here...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S FRONT HALLWAY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb glances briefly over his shoulder, towards his kitchen, then turns back to Clarice with a smile.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Mrs. Lippman had a son, maybe he could help you.
{DIALOGUE}: I have his card somewhere.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you mind stepping inside, while I looks for it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE FAVORING THE COLT PYTHON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: which rests on a counter, just inside the open kitchen doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THROUGH this doorway, we watch as Mr. Gumb, at the end of his front hall, slips the chain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice enters, closing the door behind her.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FRONT YARD OF SUSPECT'S HOUSE - CALUMET CITY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - towards the front door, as frustrated HRT cops file out of the empty house, rifles slung across their shoulders.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE PICK OUT CRAWFORD
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: walking across the grass towards the van, when all at once he stops in his tracks, shaken by a sudden flash of intuition.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA RUSHES VERY CLOSE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: on his stricken face...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Clarice.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S PARLOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice, pulling her notebook from her shoulder bag, glances around the musty-looking room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: That horrible business, I shiver every time I think about it...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Overstuffed furniture, porcelain figurines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One archway onto the front hall, another onto a dining alcove, and through there, the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb is crossing to a rolling desk, raising the top.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He bends over, begins poking through cubby holes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His tone is casual, neutral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Are they close to catching somebody, do you think?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I think we may be, yes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb stiffens, almost imperceptibly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His back is to her, as he continues opening drawers, rustling papers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Gordon, did you take over this place after Mrs. Lippman died?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: I bought the house from her, two years ago.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Did she leave any records here?
{DIALOGUE}: Tax or business records?
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe a list of employees?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON MR. GUMB'S BACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he continues his rummaging.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: No, nothing at all.
{DIALOGUE}: Has the FBI learned something?
{DIALOGUE}: Because the police here don't seem to have the first clue...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out of the folds of his kimono crawls a Death's-head Moth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It creeps slowly to the center of his back, raising its wings.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Do you have his description yet, or some fingerprints...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: unaware, is still glancing around the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: For several agonizing moments, we think she won't see the moth - but then she turns, does see it, and her eyes freeze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat of pure fear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tremendous struggle to keep her voice calm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: No... no, we don't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Very carefully, she drops her notebook back into her bag, lowers the bag to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With her fingertips she brushes back the edge of her blazer, loosening its drape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: turns back towards her cheerfully, holding out a business card.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{DIALOGUE}: Ahhh.
{DIALOGUE}: Here's that number.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: keeps her distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are about ten feet apart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Good, thank you.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Gordon, do you have a phone I can use?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is about to reply when the moth suddenly flies up from behind him, flutters past his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns, looking at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks back at Clarice, his mouth still open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER EYES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: are unmoving, locked on his.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIS EYES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: stare back at her, widen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And they know each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. GUMB
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: In the kitchen.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll show you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: whips her gun out, gripping it in both shaking hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Freeze!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: slowly tilts his head to one side, smiles at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: tries to force more authority into her voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Okay... Okay, Mr. Gumb, you're under arrest.
{DIALOGUE}: Down on the floor, hands and legs spread, move it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: turns, then all at once, in two quick steps, he is gone, disappearing into his dining alcove, then kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: hesitates, just a split second, to shoot him in the back - and then it's too late.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Shit!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S KITCHEN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice hurries inside, moving low, swivelling her gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER POV - MOVING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kitchen is empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To one side, a door still shuddering on its hinges...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: rushes to this - pauses - then elbows the door aside, aiming her gun down -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN EMPTY STAIRWELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: brightly lit, leading to the cellar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two doors facing the bottom, both open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No sign of Mr. Gumb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: hates this, hates this, which door, it's a trap, what to do: she is very scared, but suddenly hears -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The distant SCREAM of Catherine Martin, somewhere down there in that killing maze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: rushes through the doorway, and down the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEHIND HER, ON THE KITCHEN COUNTER there's an empty space; the Colt Python is gone.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S CELLAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - WITH CLARICE - hurrying down the steps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More SCREAMS; they seem to be coming from the left door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice goes that way, entering a brick-walled passage - pipes over- head, naked bulbs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lighting, though dim, is incandescent; Mr. Gumb has switched off his infra-red system.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice comes to a T-shaped intersection, stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another SCREAM, again to her left, and the BARKING of a dog...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: follows her gun around the corner, looking right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: EMPTY PASSAGEWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: but doors opening off it - he could be lurking behind any of them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks left... sees an opening onto some kind of chamber.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The noises are LOUDER, coming from there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: moves cautiously towards this chamber...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OUBLIETTE CHAMBER - DAY (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice moves in, hugging the wall, gun swivelling...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER POV - MOVING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the open top of the pit... beyond it, the other two doorways, opening onto this room - Jesus, he could come through either one of them, or come up behind her... She moves to the pit, looks down, very briefly, sees Catherine SCREAMING, hysterical, and a little white dog BARKING...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: kneels, staring up from one door to another, she can't cover them all, she's totally exposed - and what's a dog doing there?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: FBI, Catherine, you're safe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Safe, SHIT, he's got a gun!
{DIALOGUE}: Getmeout.
{DIALOGUE}: GET ME OUT!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: You're all right!
{DIALOGUE}: Where is he?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: Get me out!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: I'll get you out!
{DIALOGUE}: Just be quiet so I can hear.
{DIALOGUE}: Shut that dog up.
{META_DATA}: (still swivelling)
{DIALOGUE}: Is there a ladder?
{DIALOGUE}: Is there a rope?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know!
{DIALOGUE}: Get me out!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Catherine.
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to me.
{DIALOGUE}: I have to find a rope.
{DIALOGUE}: I have to leave this room, just for a minute, but -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATHERINE
{DIALOGUE}: NOOOOO!
{DIALOGUE}: You fucking bitch don't you LEAVE ME down here, DON'T YOU - YOU
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Shut UP!
{META_DATA}: (then, louder)
{DIALOGUE}: The other officers will be here any minute!
{DIALOGUE}: you're perfectly safe now!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ignoring Catherine, whose shouts turn to sobs, she backs away, turns, picks one of the other doorways, moves into it quickly.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NEW PASSAGEWAY - DAY (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE'S POV - MOVING down this passageway, towards a new room... pausing at the doorway, straining to hear... no sound except Catherine's CRYING, not in the background, and Clarice's own RAPID BREATHING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then she crouches -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOWER ANGLE - bursts forward, through the doorframe, sidestepping...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKROOM - DAY (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice weaves back and forth, half-crouched, gun out, back to the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her face glistens with sweat, as she takes in...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HER POV - MOVING NERVOUSLY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Gumb's sewing machine... his swivel chair... the old Victrola... Big moths are crashing into the light bulbs, overhead; they're everywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, from just behind her, a CLICK and a HUM, and -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: spins, almost shoots, before seeing -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SMALL REFRIGERATOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: with its thermostat just switching ON.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: gasps for breath, fighting for calm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns again, slashing her free hand at the moths, moving quickly on...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SKINNING ROOM - DAY (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice moves past the mannequins, all of them naked now... then quickly past the huge Chinese armoire, ready to shoot into it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its doors yawn open; it is empty except for several padded hangers... She moves on, past the big sink, with its DRIPPING faucet... the counter, with its gleaming knives... the rows of chemical jars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the end of this room is
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CLOSED DOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice starts to open it, then hesitates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking around, she seizes a wooden chair, wedges it under the door know, sealing off this section of the cellar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With her back thus defended, she turns, softly retracing her steps.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKROOM - DAY (DIMLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Passing again through the workroom, Clarice pauses, seeing a half-curtained door, to one side, that she had previously skirted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She crosses to the door, listens and hears no sound inside, takes a deep breath and reaches for the knob.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She twists it, and, as it turns, shoves hard and follows her gun inside, all in one quick move...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BATHROOM - DAY (BRIGHTLY LIT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An old-fashioned bathroom: tiled floor, sink, toilet - and a big, free-standing tub.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An opaque shower curtain, suspended from an oval ring, hides whatever might be inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: centers her gun on the curtain, at chest height, and yanks it aside with her left hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one standing there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something lower down catches her eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She leans in, stares more closely, not understanding, at first, that she's seeing -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FEMALE HAND AND WRIST
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sticking up from the tub, which is filled with hard red-purple plaster.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand is dark and shriveled, with pink nail polish and a dainty wristwatch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is reacting with horror to this sight, the lights go out, to be replaced, a split-second later, by the eerie green glow of Mr. Gumb's infra-red system.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice cries out, turns blindly, reaching for the door, can't find it, free hand clawing desperately into what is, for her, utter darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND of Catherine KEENING again, in the far distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice stumbles, goes to her knees, rights herself, finally clutches the door frame...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MR. GUMB'S WORKROOM - DAY (GREEN LIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice emerges from the bathroom in a half-crouch, arms out, both hands on the gun, extended just below the level of her unseeing eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stops, listens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In her raw-nerved darkness, every SOUND is unnaturally magnified - the HUM of the refrigerator... the TRICKLE of water... her own terrified BREATHING, and Catherine's faraway, echoing SOBS... Moths smack against her face and arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She eases forward, then stops again, listens... She eases forward again, following her gun, and creeps directly in front of, and then past -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MR. GUMB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: who has flattened himself against a wall, arms spread like a high priest, Colt in one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He wears his goggles and kimono, and under that - draping down over his naked arms, like some hideous mantle - his terrifying, half-completed suit of human skins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is an exquisite moment for him - a ritual of supreme exaltation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles at Clarice as, completely unaware, she moves beyond him, exposing her back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Very slowly and quietly he steps out behind her, taking his gun in both hands, aiming...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the Colt Python as - in SLOW MOTION - his thumbs cock the hammer, the SOUND registering as a LOUD METALLIC CLICK, and -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: spins, still in SLOW MOTION, flame already leaping from her gun muzzle, as we see -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE TWO FIGURES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: almost at point-black range, guns ROARING hugely, one FLASH from Mr. Gumb, and one two three four FLASHES from Clarice, overlapping his, and then, as the ECHOES crash deafeningly -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON CLARICE - LOW ANGLE -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: with NORMAL SPEED RESTORED, as the side of her face hits the floor, and she is gasping, stunned by the noise and flames; there is blood on her check, and an ugly powder burn, but she ignores them, twisting to yank her speedloader from her jacket pocket, locking it blindly onto her gun's cylinder, reloading, right in front of her face, then rolling onto her stomach, aiming her gun upward again, blinking her dazzled eyes, straining to locate him in the darkness... Where is he, where...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, as the ECHOES finally fade, she hears something else - a tortured, sucking, WHISTLE from perhaps eight feet away...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE - WITH CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she crawls forward, on her elbows, following her gun, until it bumps against Mr. Gumb's shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is lying on his back, chest a bloody mess.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slides her muzzle against his head, hard, but he doesn't move; another shot isn't needed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares upwards, through his goggles, bloody lips working.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries to speak, but cannot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One hand reaches slowly upwards, the fingers twitching, as if to seize something, overhead... Then a final, ghastly groan, his hand drops, he is dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice feels for a pulse at his neck, making sure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, and only then, does she permit herself to roll over, collapsing onto her back beside him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OVERHEAD ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: down at the two faces - intimately close together, like lovers on their pillow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, as we PULL SLOWLY AWAY, we see that her staring eyes, and his dead gaze, are both locked onto -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A DEATH'S-HEAD MOTH -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: perched on an infra-red bulb, overhead, its wings pumping slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND UPCUT - wailing SIRENS, many excited VOICES, as we...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MR. GUMB'S HOUSE - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front porch of the tall Victorian house is bathed in a glare of TV lights, police and ambulance flashers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cars and vans and even a firetruck choke the street; cops, reporters, EMS workers and curious civilians swarm around the ineffective barricades.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BUZZ of their voices goes even higher as
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: dazed, her face bandaged - comes out of the house, walking protectively beside Catherine, who is wheeled on a gurney.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are followed out by uniformed cops, then two firemen with an extension ladder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catherine, blinking in confusion, is still clutching the little dog, and refuses to give her up even as she's trundled into an ambulance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice sways with exhaustion; everyone seems to be shouting at her at once, pulling her sleeve.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She tries to fight free of them, desperate for a familiar face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN OHIO HIGHWAY PATROL CAR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: pulls up, stops, and Crawford climbs out of the back seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He makes his way anxiously through the press of bodies, stopping when he sees Clarice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEY LOOK AT ONE ANOTHER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: for a long moment, Crawford choked with pride for her, with sorrow for her ordeal, with love, but unable to find any words.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then he does.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CRAWFORD
{DIALOGUE}: Starling... your father sees you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then all at once she is sobbing, her knees giving way, but he is there to catch her, he is hugging her fiercely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOLD ON them for a long beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DIRECTOR BURKE (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (over loudspeaker)
{DIALOGUE}: Congratulations!
{DIALOGUE}: You are now officers of the Federal Bureau of Investigation...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GROUNDS OF THE FBI ACADEMY - WEEKS LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The forty members of Clarice's class, resplendent in their best dark suits and dresses, rise, cheering themselves, then turn happily to wave to their audience, as APPLAUSE mounts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beyond them, on a gaily tented platform, the Director stands behind his podium.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE AND ARDELIA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: look at one another solemnly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia holds up both fists, in a power shake, and Clarice taps them with her own.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is radiantly beautiful in a navy dress and pearls, the thin scar on her cheek almost healed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia turns, waving towards the crowd, the Clarice's thoughts are elsewhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns, searching among the dignitaries on the platform, till she locates
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRAWFORD
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: who smiles back at her with quiet pride, and offers a little salute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: grins - more happy than we've ever seen her - then turns to wave towards the crowd with the others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: over the admiring sea of spectators, several hundred of them, still rising from their folding chairs, APPLAUDING in celebration of these special young people, this perfect, sunlit day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND UPCUT - rock music, laughter - as we...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ACADEMY DORM - REC ROOM - THAT NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LOUD party is underway - food, beer, dancing - as the new grads celebrate ferociously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia weaves her way through the crowded room, reaches Clarice, who is flanked by her special guests - Pilcher and Roden, the two ardent scientists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia has to shout at Clarice over the din.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARDELIA
{DIALOGUE}: Agent Starling!
{DIALOGUE}: Telephone!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{META_DATA}: (surprised)
{DIALOGUE}: Agent Mapp!
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She nods to Pilcher, leaves them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Roden, who is quite happily drunk, grabs the startled Ardelia around the waist.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RODEN
{DIALOGUE}: Hel-lo, gorgeous!
{DIALOGUE}: Let's get down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia looks at Pilcher, confused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PILCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Just ignore him.
{DIALOGUE}: He's not a Ph.D.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DORM HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clarice picks up the dangling pay phone, speaks happily.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Starling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, Clarice, have the lambs stopped screaming...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She freezes, stunned by the familiar voice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then she turns, waving frantically towards
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARDELIA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: who is just inside the rec room door, at the end of the hall, lost in conversation with Pilcher and Roden.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ardelia glances at her briefly but misunderstands, waves cheerfully back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't bother with a trace, I won't be on long enough.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLARICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: turns back, gripping the phone more tightly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you, Dr. Lecter?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. A CLEAR NIGHT SKY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Very beautiful, glittering with countless stars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Where I have a view, Clarice...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING DOWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: we see a rolling lawn, a curving bay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boats ride at anchor, lights shimmering...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Orion is looking splendid tonight, and Arcturus, the Herdsman, with his flock...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DR. LECTER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: smiles into his mobile phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is stretched out on a lounger, on a tiled patio, languidly paring an orange with a penknife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His appearance is quite altered - a beard, glasses, lighter hair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's has some cosmetic surgery, as well.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Your lambs are still for now, Clarice, but not forever... You'll have to earn it again and again, this blessed silence.
{DIALOGUE}: Because it's the plight that drives you, and the plight will never end.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Lecter -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: I have no plans to call on you, Clarice, the world being more interesting with you in it.
{DIALOGUE}: Be sure you extend me the same courtesy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: You know I can't make that promise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye, Clarice...
{META_DATA}: (and then, softly)
{DIALOGUE}: You looked - so very lovely today, in your blue suit.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DORM HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Clarice reacts, the fill weight of his words sinking in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLARICE
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Lecter... Dr. Lecter...!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But only a DIAL TONE comes from the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is still staring at her receiver, in shock, as we -
{META_DATA}: CUT BACK TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE MOONLIT PATIO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dr. Lecter sighs, sets his phone down, then rises.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Popping an orange section into his mouth, he turns towards the brightly lit house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stepping delicately over the sprawled body of a uniformed security guard, he walks in through open french doors.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. A BOOKLINED STUDY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a swivel chair, amidst the wreckage of his papers and books, is the writhing figure of Dr. Frederick Chilton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The extreme intricacy of his bindings recalls Dr. Lecter's own former restraints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His screams are muffled by the tape over his mouth; he stares at Dr. Lecter like a rabbit trapped in headlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DR. LECTER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Considers him for a genial moment, then raises the little pen-knife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes are twinkling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DR. LECTER
{DIALOGUE}: Well, Dr. Chilton.
{DIALOGUE}: Shall we begin?
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT
{META_DATA}: THE END
